  "title": "Posterior compartment of leg",
  "body_html": "The posterior compartment of the leg is supplied by the tibial nerve.<br /><br />There are 4 deep muscles:<br /><ul><li>Tibialis posterior</li><li>Flexor digitorum longus</li><li>Flexor hallucis longus</li><li>Popliteus</li></ul>There are 3 superficial muscles:<br /><ul><li>Gastrocnemius</li><li>Plantaris</li><li>Soleus</li></ul><br /><br /><br /><i>Diagram illustrating posterior compartment of leg</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073b.gif'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073.gif'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posterior compartment of leg'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073b.gif'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Video tutorial on the posterior compartment of leg</i><br /><br /><iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/F1J0HbV2n5s' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">3</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Lower limb anatomy</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe posterior compartment of the leg is supplied by the tibial nerve.<br /><br />There are 4 deep muscles:<br /><ul><li>Tibialis posterior</li><li>Flexor digitorum longus</li><li>Flexor hallucis longus</li><li>Popliteus</li></ul>There are 3 superficial muscles:<br /><ul><li>Gastrocnemius</li><li>Plantaris</li><li>Soleus</li></ul><br /><br /><br /><i>Diagram illustrating posterior compartment of leg</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073b.gif'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073.gif'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posterior compartment of leg'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb073b.gif'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Video tutorial on the posterior compartment of leg</i><br /><br /><iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/F1J0HbV2n5s' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><br><br>",
